From fresh jetpack installation: 

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get -y install python3-pip
sudo apt-get update
pip3 install -U numpy

follow this tutorial to install servokit/busio/board @ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RnGUTny1hG8

Set the Machines IP Address to a static value:
	Click the internet connections button
	Edit Connections
	Double Click Ethernet Connection
	IPv4 settings
	Add "Address : xxx.yyy.zzz.QQQ Netmask : 255.255.255.0"

Copy the code from github manually by using the 'git clone' command or add it using a flashdrive

The main function is UWFInvertedPendulum/Python/liveAngleMeasurement.py 
***It must be run with Python3

Notes:
Using VNCServer to share the desktop...See 'Desktop Sharing' Instructions
After making a static IP Address you will lose connection to the UWF Internet. They do not allow static IPs (but it is still safe)

